		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Specialization<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 1:06 AM 2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=96657521813044&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=96657521813044&num=7&post=1&replyto=96657521813044"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=96657521813044></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=321"><span id=>Quimby</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>10 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.33]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>There are a great many debates and discussions over which specialization is best. I believe you should choose the specialization that best suits your playing style.<br><br>If you prefer to solo, Evocation is the way to go as "burn, baby, burn!" is a great tactic for such.<br><br>Many higher level druids prefer to solo via the tactic of "Root, DoT, Meditate, Repeat" which easily require a hefty Conjuration skill for an efficient solo experience.<br><br>Other druids spend most of their existence as primary healer for fast-paced energetic groups.&nbsp;&nbsp;This tends to lean them in the ways of Alteration.<br><br>Your play style may vary as you progress in levels. Let your specialization vary as well if need be.<br><br>My personal experience started my druid life out on Evocation as Ignite becomes a nice favorite in your early levels.  At level 14 you suddenly need a quick amount of Conjuration skill as Stinging Swarm comes into play. I swayed back and forth between using Evocation based spells and Conjurations based ones before finding the best technique for me.<br><br>As you reach 35+ and especially 50+, the need for specializing in anything but Alteration starts to slowly wither away. At level 53, you will need Specialization in Alteration to efficiently cast Superior Healing.  Without it, you will fall prey to fizzle after fizzle. <br><br>Like I stated before, each druid needs to use the specialization that best suits their playing style.  Don't be afraid to change specializations either.  Good ole' Ostorm in the Temple of Solusek Ro will be happy to fix you up for 50gp and a Ruby.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Quimby Thistlebritches<br>Druid of Karana<br><br>Sacred Order of Shadows</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >7 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 3:15 AM 2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=96657521813044&num=7&post=1&replyto=96658292422138"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=96658292422138></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I would say, that Evocation is the only specialization a druid needs. The skill is useful for using less mana and fewer fizzles, so it is best suited for combat spells. And the only ones which have to be delivered fast and hopefully cheap, are your DDs, which are all evocations, up to the 59th uber spell. <br><br>I grant, that Superior Heal also falls into this category, but it doesnt have that high a mana cost as many DDs, and it is only one spell.<br><br>For DoTs there is another reasoning...they are pretty mana efficient and you dont have to use that many on your victim(s), and it is usually no catastrophe, when you fizzle one (besides, a few of them are evocations...).</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
