		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=614"><span id=>Ervyn</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>2 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>When I had to choose my specialization, I though to myself, "What spell am I likely to cast in a pinch that will win or lose my/a groupmate's life?"<br><br>Let's cover the most poular:<br><br>Evocation - killing the mob before he kills you/your groupmate- undeniably needed sometimes.<br><br>Alteration - This one is most often referred to as healing- but let's not forget what else uses alteration, perhaps the most important job a druid has at high levels- EVAC.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is probably the spell that will save you and your group more than anything else.<br><br>Conjuration - doesn't really apply unless they you/your group is dying of hunger or thirst (woo!  Summon water!)<br><br><br>Thus (as you may have guessed) I chose alteration.  I prefer to get that last heal off when the cleric is oom or be able to evac when you're really low on mana.<br><br>Anyway, just my two cents.<br><br>Ervyn Peregrinus<br>40th Druid of Tunare<br><br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Reality is for those who can't face Science Fiction</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
